  200. ‌type description =

  208.     (* The compiler version introducing this warning; only tagged for warnings
  209.        created after 3.12, which introduced the numbered syntax. *)

  601. let backup () = !current

  621. let with_state state f =
  622.   let prev = backup () in
  623.   restore state;
  624.   try
  625.     let r = f () in
  626.     restore prev;
  627.     r
  628.   with exn ->
  629.     restore prev;
  630.     raise exn

  632. let mk_lazy f =

  636. let set_alert ~error ~enable s =
  637.   let upd =
  638.     match s with
  639.     | "all" ->
  640.         (Misc.Stdlib.String.Set.empty, not enable)
  641.     | s ->
  642.         let (set, pos) =
  643.           if error then (!current).alert_errors else (!current).alerts
  644.         in
  645.         let f =
  646.           if enable = pos
  647.           then Misc.Stdlib.String.Set.add
  648.           else Misc.Stdlib.String.Set.remove
  649.         in
  650.         (f s set, pos)
  651.   in
  652.   if error then
  653.     current := {(!current) with alert_errors=upd}
  654.   else
  655.     current := {(!current) with alerts=upd}

  657. let parse_alert_option s =
  658.   let n = String.length s in
  659.   let id_char = function
  660.     | 'a'..'z' | 'A'..'Z' | '_' | '\'' | '0'..'9' -> true
  661.     | _ -> false
  662.   in
  663.   let rec parse_id i =
  664.     if i < n && id_char s.[i] then parse_id (i + 1) else i
  665.   in
  666.   let rec scan i =
  667.     if i = n then ()
  668.     else if i + 1 = n then raise (Arg.Bad "Ill-formed list of alert settings")
  669.     else match s.[i], s.[i+1] with
  670.       | '+', '+' -> id (set_alert ~error:true ~enable:true) (i + 2)
  671.       | '+', _ -> id (set_alert ~error:false ~enable:true) (i + 1)
  672.       | '-', '-' -> id (set_alert ~error:true ~enable:false) (i + 2)
  673.       | '-', _ -> id (set_alert ~error:false ~enable:false) (i + 1)
  674.       | '@', _ ->
  675.           id (fun s ->
  676.               set_alert ~error:true ~enable:true s;
  677.               set_alert ~error:false ~enable:true s)
  678.             (i + 1)
  679.       | _ -> raise (Arg.Bad "Ill-formed list of alert settings")
  680.   and id f i =
  681.     let j = parse_id i in
  682.     if j = i then raise (Arg.Bad "Ill-formed list of alert settings");
  683.     let id = String.sub s i (j - i) in
  684.     f id;
  685.     scan j
  686.   in
  687.   scan 0

  689. type modifier =
  690.   | Set (** +a *)
  691.   | Clear (** -a *)
  692.   | Set_all (** @a *)

  694. type token =
  695.   | Letter of char * modifier option
  696.   | Num of int * int * modifier

  698. let ghost_loc_in_file name =
  699.   let pos = { Lexing.dummy_pos with pos_fname = name } in
  700.   { loc_start = pos; loc_end = pos; loc_ghost = true }

  702. let letter_alert tokens =
  703.   let print_warning_char ppf c =
  704.     let lowercase = Char.lowercase_ascii c = c in
  705.     Format.fprintf ppf "%c%c"
  706.       (if lowercase then '-' else '+') c
  707.   in
  708.   let print_modifier ppf = function
  709.     | Set_all -> Format.fprintf ppf "@"
  710.     | Clear -> Format.fprintf ppf "-"
  711.     | Set -> Format.fprintf ppf "+"
  712.   in
  713.   let print_token ppf = function
  714.     | Num (a,b,m) -> if a = b then
  715.           Format.fprintf ppf "%a%d" print_modifier m a
  716.         else
  717.           Format.fprintf ppf "%a%d..%d" print_modifier m a b
  718.     | Letter(l,Some m) -> Format.fprintf ppf "%a%c" print_modifier m l
  719.     | Letter(l,None) -> print_warning_char ppf l
  720.   in
  721.   let consecutive_letters =
  722.     (* we are tracking sequences of 2 or more consecutive unsigned letters
  723.        in warning strings, for instance in '-w "not-principa"'. *)
  724.     let commit_chunk l = function
  725.       | [] | [ _ ] -> l
  726.       | _ :: _ :: _ as chunk -> List.rev chunk :: l
  727.     in
  728.     let group_consecutive_letters (l,current) = function
  729.     | Letter (x, None) -> (l, x::current)
  730.     | _ -> (commit_chunk l current, [])
  731.     in
  732.     let l, on_going =
  733.       List.fold_left group_consecutive_letters ([],[]) tokens
  734.     in
  735.     commit_chunk l on_going
  736.   in
  737.   match consecutive_letters with
  738.   | [] -> None
  739.   | example :: _  ->
  740.       let nowhere = ghost_loc_in_file "_none_" in
  741.       let spelling_hint ppf =
  742.         let max_seq_len =
  743.           List.fold_left (fun l x -> Int.max l (List.length x))
  744.             0 consecutive_letters
  745.         in
  746.         if max_seq_len >= 5 then
  747.           Format.fprintf ppf
  748.             "@ @[Hint: Did you make a spelling mistake \
  749.              when using a mnemonic name?@]"
  750.         else
  751.           ()
  752.       in
  753.       let message =
  754.         Format.asprintf
  755.           "@[<v>@[Setting a warning with a sequence of lowercase \
  756.            or uppercase letters,@ like '%a',@ is deprecated.@]@ \
  757.            @[Use the equivalent signed form:@ %t.@]@ \
  758.            @[Hint: Enabling or disabling a warning by its mnemonic name \
  759.            requires a + or - prefix.@]\
  760.            %t@?@]"
  761.           Format.(pp_print_list ~pp_sep:(fun _ -> ignore) pp_print_char) example
  762.           (fun ppf -> List.iter (print_token ppf) tokens)
  763.           spelling_hint
  764.       in
  765.       Some {
  766.         kind="ocaml_deprecated_cli";
  767.         use=nowhere; def=nowhere;
  768.         message
  769.       }


  772. let parse_warnings s =
  773.   let error () = raise (Arg.Bad "Ill-formed list of warnings") in
  774.   let rec get_num n i =
  775.     if i >= String.length s then i, n
  776.     else match s.[i] with
  777.     | '0'..'9' -> get_num (10 * n + Char.code s.[i] - Char.code '0') (i + 1)
  778.     | _ -> i, n
  779.   in
  780.   let get_range i =
  781.     let i, n1 = get_num 0 i in
  782.     if i + 2 < String.length s && s.[i] = '.' && s.[i + 1] = '.' then
  783.       let i, n2 = get_num 0 (i + 2) in
  784.       if n2 < n1 then error ();
  785.       i, n1, n2
  786.     else
  787.       i, n1, n1
  788.   in
  789.   let rec loop tokens i =
  790.     if i >= String.length s then List.rev tokens else
  791.     match s.[i] with
  792.     | 'A' .. 'Z' | 'a' .. 'z' ->
  793.         loop (Letter(s.[i],None)::tokens) (i+1)
  794.     | '+' -> loop_letter_num tokens Set (i+1)
  795.     | '-' -> loop_letter_num tokens Clear (i+1)
  796.     | '@' -> loop_letter_num tokens Set_all (i+1)
  797.     | _ -> error ()
  798.   and loop_letter_num tokens modifier i =
  799.     if i >= String.length s then error () else
  800.     match s.[i] with
  801.     | '0' .. '9' ->
  802.         let i, n1, n2 = get_range i in
  803.         loop (Num(n1,n2,modifier)::tokens) i
  804.     | 'A' .. 'Z' | 'a' .. 'z' ->
  805.        loop (Letter(s.[i],Some modifier)::tokens) (i+1)
  806.     | _ -> error ()
  807.   in
  808.   loop [] 0

  810. let parse_opt error active errflag s =
  811.   let flags = if errflag then error else active in
  812.   let action modifier i = match modifier with
  813.     | Set ->
  814.         if i = 3 then set_alert ~error:errflag ~enable:true "deprecated"
  815.         else flags.(i) <- true
  816.     | Clear ->
  817.         if i = 3 then set_alert ~error:errflag ~enable:false "deprecated"
  818.         else flags.(i) <- false
  819.     | Set_all ->
  820.         if i = 3 then begin
  821.           set_alert ~error:false ~enable:true "deprecated";
  822.           set_alert ~error:true ~enable:true "deprecated"
  823.         end
  824.         else begin
  825.           active.(i) <- true;
  826.           error.(i) <- true
  827.         end
  828.   in
  829. ‌  let eval = function
  830.     | Letter(c, m) ->
  831.         let lc = Char.lowercase_ascii c in
  832.         let modifier = match m with
  833.           | None -> if c = lc then Clear else Set
  834.           | Some m -> m
  835.         in
  836.         List.iter (action modifier) (letter lc)
  837.     | Num(n1,n2,modifier) ->
  838.         for n = n1 to Int.min n2 last_warning_number do action modifier n done
  839.   in
  840. ‌  let parse_and_eval s =
  841.     let tokens = parse_warnings s in
  842.     List.iter eval tokens;
  843.     letter_alert tokens
  844.   in
  845.    match name_to_number s with
  846.   | Some n -> action Set n; None
  847.   | None ->
  848.       if s = "" then parse_and_eval s
  849.       else begin
  850. ‌        let rest = String.sub s 1 (String.length s - 1) in
  851.         match s.[0], name_to_number rest with
  852.         | '+', Some n -> action Set n; None
  853.         | '-', Some n -> action Clear n; None
  854.         | '@', Some n -> action Set_all n; None
  855.         | _ -> parse_and_eval s
  856.       end

  858. ‌let parse_options errflag s =

  860.   let active = Array.copy (!current).active in

  862.   current := {(!current) with error; active};
  863.   alerts

  980.      end
  981.   | Unused_rec_flag ->

  983.   | Name_out_of_scope (ty, [nm], false) ->

  991.       ^ String.concat " " slist ^ ".\n\
